benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/{customFieldId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve custom field audit logs with history by id

covered: GET method Valid Request scenarios (TC01) for existing custom field
Empty Response handling (TC02) when no audit logs exist
Error handling for non-existent custom field (TC03)
Edge case: very large number of logs and performance expectations (TC11)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not explicitly tested (e.g., page size, page token, and total count in responses)
Caching behavior not tested (ETag/Cache-Control headers and client-side caching implications)
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios for rapid successive requests
Authorization coverage beyond 401 (e.g., 403 forbidden when user lacks permissions)
Detailed validation of response schemas beyond presence of fields (e.g., strict schema validation or schema versioning)
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify correct behavior with large result sets (page size, page, total count, and links if applicable).
Add tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and revalidation behavior.
Add rate limiting/throttle scenarios to ensure the API handles high-request volume gracefully.
Add authorization tests for insufficient permissions (403) to complement 401/Authentication tests.
Add deeper schema validation checks to ensure response objects strictly conform to the AuditLog schema.
